```
GeneMark-ETP initially predicted 11,992 genes, while AUGUSTUS predicted 14,334 genes.\
After integration, BUSCO rescue, internal stop codon filtering, and CDS normalization, the final gene set contained 14,389 genes and 16,774 transcripts.

## Completeness assessment

| Dataset  | Tool      | Complete | Fragmented | Missing |
| -------- | --------- | -------: | ---------: | ------: |
| Genome   | BUSCO     |    98.8% |       0.2% |    1.0% |
| Genome   | compleasm |    99.2% |       0.5% |    0.4% |
| Proteome | BUSCO     |    91.5% |       5.2% |    3.3% |
| Proteome | compleasm |    92.3% |       5.0% |    2.7% |

The genome assembly showed high completeness, with approximately 99% of conserved fungal genes detected.\
Proteome completeness was lower at approximately 92%, indicating that some conserved genes present in the genome may not have been completely reconstructed in the predicted gene models.

Compleasm reported a high duplicated BUSCO proportion in the proteome. 
This should be re-evaluated using one representative protein isoform per gene because `braker.aa` may contain multiple transcript isoforms from the same locus.

